https://www.mimuw.edu.pl/~miekisz/matuszakoptymaltran.pdf
    - approximate solutions 2012

https://arxiv.org/pdf/2003.13797:
    - very interesting
    - There exist very efficient algorithms in a planar geometry providing a globally optimal Steiner tree
    (see for instance the GeoSteiner method [ 21] or Melzak’s full Steiner tree algorithm [26]).
    - For the general transportation network problem, a widely used approach was inspired by elliptic approximations of
    free-discontinuity problems in the sense of Modica–Mortola and Ambrosio–Tortorelli via phase fields. In [29, 12, 27, 17, 16, 37 ]


